      • shareText

        public static void shareText(android.content.Context ctx,
                             java.lang.String sText)
        Opens the OS-standard "share" dialog, using the specified text content to be shared. The title of the dialog is defaulted to the value of R.string#title_diaShare_default provided by this library, which may be overridden in the app that consumes this library.
        Parameters:
        ctx - the context in which to operate
        sText - the text to be shared

      • tweetText

        public static void tweetText(android.content.Context ctx,
                             java.lang.String sTweet)
                      throws java.io.UnsupportedEncodingException
        Dispatches an intent to view Twitter's "tweet" intent page, using the specified text as the contents of the tweet. This will usually trigger either the Twitter app or a browser window to open, allowing the user to confirm the tweet.
        Parameters:
        ctx - the context in which to attempt the tweet
        sTweet - the tweet text
        Throws:
        java.io.UnsupportedEncodingException - if the tweet text cannot be URL-encoded in UTF-8, as specified within the function

      • tryToTweetText

        public static boolean tryToTweetText(android.content.Context ctx,
                                     java.lang.String sTweet)
        As tweetText(Context, String), but catches the possible UnsupportedEncodingException internally, by logging an error.
        Parameters:
        ctx - the context in which to attempt the tweet
        sTweet - the tweet text
        Returns:
        true if the attempt succeeded, or false if an UnsupportedEncodingException was caught
